(Regression) (Analysis)

  • (independent variable), (dependent variable)
  • (Explanatory variable), (Response variable)
  • (Predictor variable), (Outcome variable)

\[ \mathbb{E}[Y | x_1, x_2, ..., x_p] = f(x_1, x_2, ..., x_p) \]

(Simple Linear Regression)

\[ y= \beta_0 + \beta_1 x + e, e \sim N(0, \sigma^2)\] \[ E[Y | x] = \beta_0 + \beta_1 x + e \]

(LINE)

  • Linearity() : (predictor) 1 , (outcome variable) .
  • Independence() : , .
  • Normality() : .
  • Equal variance() : (homoscedasticity). (heteroscedasticity) .

dat <- read.csv(file='./LR_weight_n100.csv', header=T, row.names=1)

# 01.  
ggplot(dat, aes(x= gender, y=weight)) + geom_point() + labs(title="01.  ")

# 02.

# 03.   
## a
plot(weight ~ gender, dat, main='03.    a');
datModel <- model.matrix(~gender+weight, dat)

plot(weight ~ genderM, datModel)
fitLmModel <- lm(weight ~ genderM, data.frame(datModel))
abline(fitLmModel)

## b
ggplot(data.frame(datModel), aes(x=genderM, y=weight)) + geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method="lm") + labs(title='03.    b')

  • \(y\) \(y\)
    • (MSE; Mean Squared Error) : \(\frac{\sum{(\hat{y_i}-y_i)^2}}{n}\)
    • (RMSE; Root Mean Squared Error) : \(\sqrt{\frac{(\sum{\hat{y_i}-y_i)^2}}{n}}\)
    • (MAE; Mean Absolute Error) : \(\frac{\sum{|\hat{y_i}-y_i|}}{n}\)
    • (the coefficient of determination) : \(R^2 = \mathbb{C}or(y, \hat{y})^2 = \frac{\mathbb{V}\text{ar}[y]-\text{MSE}}{\mathbb{V}\text{ar}[y]}\)

## Loading required package: lattice
# 01. lm(weight ~ height, dat) lm(weight ~ gender, dat)
dat <- read.csv(file='./LR_weight_n100.csv', header=T, row.names=1)
fitA <- lm(weight ~ height, dat)
fitB <- lm(weight ~ gender, dat)

# 02.  
## MSE
mean((dat$weight - predict(fitA))^2)
## [1] 152.8368
mean((dat$weight - predict(fitB))^2)
## [1] 195.8862

## RMSE
RMSE(dat$weight, predict(fitA)) #sqrt(mean((dat$weight - predict(fitA))^2))
## [1] 12.36272
RMSE(dat$weight, predict(fitB)) #sqrt(mean((dat$weight - predict(fitB))^2))
## [1] 13.99593

## MAE
MAE(dat$weight, predict(fitA)) 
## [1] 9.88135
RMSE(dat$weight, predict(fitB))
## [1] 13.99593

## 
summary(fitA)$r.squared # cor(dat$weight, predict(fitA))^2
## [1] 0.6416205
summary(fitB)$r.squared
## [1] 0.540676
